# Identity bridge: our user_id ≠ engine player_id
The engine's `player_id` is its **own** UUID (`users.id`); our user id is stored there
as `external_id`. A player must be provisioned before any bet/win/purchase or the engine
returns `PLAYER_NOT_FOUND`.
- On registration call `POST /api/v1/player/create` with `external_id = <our user id>`
  and persist the returned `player_id` into `User.trueEnginePlayerId`.
- Provisioning is idempotent on `external_id`; a self-healing
  `resolveTrueEnginePlayerId()` may lazily provision on first transaction.
- All engine calls send `player_id = user.trueEnginePlayerId`, never our raw user id.

